Description: Bronze finger-ring; flattened oval bezel with engraved design: grotesque figure wearing uraeus crown(?), and holding one stick with his raised left and another with his lowered right hand.
Bibliographic references: Finger Ring / Catalogue of the Finger Rings, Greek, Etruscan, and Roman, in the Departments of Antiquities, British Museum (1309)
Acquisition name: Bequeathed by: Sir Augustus Wollaston Franks
